            <title><![CDATA[Kanon for Switch update to add English and Simplified Chinese language support on December 5]]></title>
            <link>https://www.gematsu.com/2024/11/kanon-for-switch-update-to-add-english-and-simplified-chinese-language-support-on-december-5</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/kanon-for-switch-update-to-add-english-and-simplified-chinese-language-support-on-december-5.1041393/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://www.gematsu.com/2024/11/kanon-for-switch-update-to-add-english-and-simplified-chinese-language-support-on-december-5<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>Worldwide release incoming?</span>
      </p></div><div><p>The <a title="Platforms > Switch [16,331 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a> version of <a title="Genres > Romance Visual Novel [63 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/visual-novel/romance-visual-novel">romance visual novel</a> <em><a title="Games > Kanon [2 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/kanon">Kanon</a></em>, which <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2023/01/kanon-for-switch-launches-april-20-in-japan">launched</a> on April 20, 2023 in Japan, will be updated with English and Simplified Chinese language options on December 5, publisher <a title="Companies > PROTOTYPE [109 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/prototype">PROTOTYPE</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/PROTOTYPE_info/status/1859468405738439141" rel="noopener" target="_blank">announced</a>. The opening movie will also be viewable in all three available languages (English, Japanese, and Simplified Korean). <span id="more-929202"></span></p><p>The new languages are likely the same translations used for the PC version of <em>Kanon</em> that launched via <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2850310/Kanon/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Steam</a> on June 20 worldwide.</p><p>While not announced, this update might also suggest the Switch version of <em>Kanon</em> will be released worldwide on the same date, as the publisher’s <a title="Genres > Visual Novel [485 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/visual-novel">visual novel games</a> normally launch day-and-date worldwide when an English language option is available.</p></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
        </item>
